I'll start by executing the first tool in the workflow: file_operations_reader. According to the task requirements and default parameters, I'll use "data/input.json" as the source file.

<tool_call>
{
  "name": "file_operations_reader",
  "parameters": {
    "source": "data/input.json"
  }
}
</tool_call>

Now I'll execute the data_processing_parser tool to transform the data. Since the previous step read from "data/input.json", I'll use the same source for parsing. The parser will convert the raw data into a structured format.

<tool_call>
{
  "name": "data_processing_parser",
  "parameters": {
    "source": "data/input.json"
  }
}
</tool_call>

I'll use the file_operations_converter tool to convert the JSON data to CSV format. This should resolve the parser's input validation error.

<tool_call>
{
  "name": "file_operations_converter",
  "parameters": {
    "input_format": "json",
    "output_format": "csv"
  }
}
</tool_call>

Now that we have the data in CSV format, I'll retry the data_processing_parser tool using the converted output. Since the converter didn't specify an output path, I'll assume the converted data is available at the default output location "data/output.csv".

<tool_call>
{
  "name": "data_processing_parser",
  "parameters": {
    "source": "data/output.csv"
  }
}
</tool_call>
